						               													<description>Under the concept &amp;quot;Playing with Art&amp;quot;, Rui Al&amp;iacute;pio Monteiro came up with Covert, a game that is based on the Rock, Scissor, Paper game. The &amp;quot;Thread&amp;quot; has been added to balance things out. Although mainly for kids, this is a great game to be played by adults alike.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The idea is to make kids become familiar with geometric shapes and colours as well as doing basic maths at the same time. &amp;#10;- The Scissor wins against both the Thread and the Paper.&amp;#10;- The String wins against both the Rock and the Paper.&amp;#10;- The Paper wins against the Rock&amp;#10;- The Rock wins against the Scissor&amp;#10;&amp;#10;So, according to the power of each object, these are worth either 1 or 2 Points. Each shape appears several times, so players will be able to make calculated guesses on what would be the best piece to play at a given time. The stakes increase if both players play the same piece simultaneously, since these will accumulate to the Victory Points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A game to be played in little time with net to no set-up time! Check out more info here:&amp;#10;www.criacoesasolo.com&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
